text.section:
A resolution authorizing the issuance of bonds under this subtitle shall determine and specify:
The date or dates of issue;
The date or dates and amount or amounts of maturities, which need not be in equal principal amounts or consecutive annual installments, but a bond may not be issued to mature later than 30 years after the date of its issue;
The rate or rates of interest payable on the bonds, or the manner of determining the rate or rates of interest, and the date or dates of payment of interest;
The tenor, form or forms, denomination or denominations, manner of execution, and place or places of payment of the principal of and interest on the bonds, which may be by any bank or trust company within or without this State;
Whether the bonds are to be issued in coupon, registered or book entry form and whether provision is to be made for the registration of the principal only of coupon bonds, for the reconversion of fully registered bonds into coupon form, and for the replacement of bonds that are mutilated, lost, or destroyed;
Whether the bonds are to be sold at public or private sale, as determined by the Secretary;
If the bonds are to be sold at public sale, the form of notice of sale, which shall outline the terms and conditions of the sale, and the form of advertisement of a summary notice of sale, which shall be published at least once in an appropriate newspaper of general circulation as determined by the Secretary;
Whether all or any part of the bonds are redeemable before maturity and, if so, the terms, conditions, and prices of redemption; and
Any other matter relating to the form, terms, conditions, issuance, sale, and delivery of the bonds.
